---

<Layout title="eCitizen Services">
  <Container>
    <section>
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-6">Cyber Services</h1>
      <details class="mb-6 border border-gray-300 rounded-md shadow-md transition-all duration-500">
        <summary class="px-4 py-2 bg-gray-100 cursor-pointer outline-none text-lg font-bold mb-2">1. E-CITIZEN</summary>
        <div class="px-4 py-2">
          <p class="mb-2">Create an account on eCitizen platform following these steps:</p>
          <ol class="list-decimal pl-6">
            <li>Open your browser and go to the eCitizen website.</li>
            <li>Click on the "Create Account" tab on the right-hand side of the screen.</li>
            <li>
              Choose the type of account you want to create:
              <ul class="list-disc pl-6">
                <li>Kenyan Citizen</li>
                <li>Foreign Residents</li>
                <li>Visitors</li>
                <li>Business</li>
              </ul>
            </li>
            <li>Follow the on-screen instructions to complete the process.</li>
          </ol>
        </div>
      </details>
      <details class="border border-gray-300 rounded-md shadow-md transition-all duration-500">
        <summary class="px-4 py-2 bg-gray-100 cursor-pointer outline-none text-lg font-bold mb-2">2. Birth Certificate Application</summary>
        <div class="px-4 py-2">
          <p class="mb-2">Submission Requirements:</p>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6">
            <li>Scanned copy of a birth notification</li>
            <li>Scanned copy of National ID for applicants over 18 years</li>
            <li>Scanned copy of a parent’s ID</li>
            <li>Scanned copy of an original birth certificate for replacements</li>
            <li>Payment of application fees</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="mb-2">Application steps:</p>
          <ol class="list-decimal pl-6">
            <li>Sign in to eCitizen.</li>
            <li>Fill in an online form and upload relevant documents in PDF format.</li>
            <li>Choose the type of birth certificate application.</li>
            <li>Attach scanned copies of required documents.</li>
            <li>Choose a pickup location for the certificate.</li>
            <li>Complete payment using Mpesa.</li>
          </ol>
        </div>
      </details>
      <details class="border border-gray-300 rounded-md shadow-md transition-all duration-500">
        <summary class="px-4 py-2 bg-gray-100 cursor-pointer outline-none text-lg font-bold mb-2">3. Good Conduct</summary>
        <div class="px-4 py-2">
          <p>Follow these steps to apply for a Good Conduct Certificate:</p>
          <ol class="list-decimal pl-6">
            <li>Log in to your eCitizen account and sign in using your username (your email address) and password, redirecting you to the eCitizen dashboard.</li>
            <li>Click "Get Service Now," which is under the category "Directorate of Criminal Investigations." Follow the application guidelines.</li>
            <li>Choose the payment mode to pay Ksh. 1,050 via M-Pesa for the Good Conduct Certificate to be processed.</li>
            <li>Download the certificate of good conduct and print two copies of the payment invoice and a copy of the C24 form on both sides of the A4 paper. Proceed to present the document to the nearest CID offices once you complete the online application.</li>
            <li>You are required to carry the invoice, C24 document, and an original identification document or original birth certificate in the case of a minor. CID personnel will take you through fingerprint processing at the divisional CID offices or a Huduma Centre near you.</li>
          </ol>
        </div>
      </details>
    </section>
  </Container>
</Layout>